Consider an object moving at constant acceleration&nbsp;\(a\)&nbsp;from initial velocity&nbsp;\(u\)&nbsp;to velocity&nbsp;\(v\)&nbsp;at time&nbsp;\(t\)<br><ol><li>The displacement moved in this time is&nbsp;\(s=\frac{(u+v)t}{2}\)</li><li>The area under the graph is a trapezium with area&nbsp;\(\frac{(u+v)t}{2}\)</li></ol><div>So it gives the displacement.</div>